Users must not submit private keys, secrets, credentials, keystore passwords,
API tokens, session tokens, authorization headers, cookies, or other sensitive
material to CryptView or to this Splunk app.

The Splunk app visualizes CryptView-generated data. It does not perform active
scans from Splunk, run PQC probes from Splunk, or include the CryptView
Collector/CLI. The CryptView Collector/CLI is separate software and must be run
outside Splunk by authorized users.

PQC readiness results are evidence-based and not a certification. Standard
TLS-only evidence does not prove PQC transport support or lack of support.
CryptView reports PQC transport as "not tested" unless active or otherwise
proven PQC transport evidence exists.

